{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17623411","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17623411"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T16:10:58+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T16:10:58+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16864"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"16864","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/16864"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.73,0,0.25,0,0.02]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9554"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"67385"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"9554","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/9554"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16864"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"52837"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4911"},{"type":"tags","id":"4926"},{"type":"tags","id":"4929"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"4943"},{"type":"tags","id":"5057"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"22567"},{"type":"contributions","id":"22571"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"67385","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/67385"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EAdrenaline is released from the adrenal medulla during the \u0027fight or flight\u0027 response, producing widespread effects throughout the body.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the cardiovascular effects of adrenaline?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Increases heart rate with vasodilation in skeletal muscle and vasoconstriction in skin","Decreases heart rate with vasoconstriction in all vascular beds","Increases heart rate with vasoconstriction in skeletal muscle and vasodilation in skin","Decreases heart rate with vasodilation in all vascular beds","Has no effect on heart rate with vasoconstriction in all vascular beds"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIncreases heart rate with vasodilation in skeletal muscle and vasoconstriction in skin\u003C/strong\u003E is correct. Adrenaline stimulates beta-1 receptors in the heart to increase rate and contractility. It causes vasodilation in skeletal muscle and liver through beta-2 receptors while causing vasoconstriction in skin, viscera, and kidneys through alpha-1 receptors.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDecreases heart rate with vasoconstriction in all vascular beds\u003C/strong\u003E - Adrenaline increases rather than decreases heart rate and causes selective vasodilation in metabolically active tissues\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIncreases heart rate with vasoconstriction in skeletal muscle and vasodilation in skin\u003C/strong\u003E - The pattern of vasodilation/vasoconstriction is reversed from the actual effects\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDecreases heart rate with vasodilation in all vascular beds\u003C/strong\u003E - Adrenaline increases heart rate and causes selective rather than widespread vasodilation\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHas no effect on heart rate with vasoconstriction in all vascular beds\u003C/strong\u003E - Adrenaline has direct chronotropic effects and does not cause universal vasoconstriction\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThis pattern of vascular responses helps direct blood flow to metabolically active tissues like skeletal muscle while reducing flow to less essential vascular beds during the stress response.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Adrenaline increases heart rate and contractility through beta-1 adrenergic receptor activation.","Adrenaline causes vasoconstriction in skin, viscera, and kidneys through alpha-1 adrenergic receptor activation.","Adrenaline causes vasodilation in skeletal muscle and liver through beta-2 adrenergic receptor activation."],"references":["Tortora GJ, Derrickson BH, Burkett B, Peoples G, Dye D, Cooke J, et al. Principles of Anatomy and Physiology, 2nd Asia-Pacific Edition: John Wiley \u0026 Sons, Limited; 2019"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"52837"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16864"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"52837","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/52837"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-05T09:48:04+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-05T09:48:56+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9554"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"67385"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (ident